rComments: Pretty effective teacher. Exams tend to be a bit on the tricky side of things but hes pretty good at what he does overall.

All the homework was practical exercises and applications. The same with previous tests he had administered. Our tests came and they were nothing like our homework and referred to things he mentioned in passing in class. Be careful, very careful. He's very unforgiving of the consequences his own mistakes.

Excellent handwriting and clear and coherent lectures. Very straight forward class, tests are very obvious problems but require a lot of conceptual thinking the way he writes them. Interesting lecture to go to. Has his stupid moments.

Excellent Prof when it comes to lectures, grades rather harshly, homework policy sucks monkey balls, exams on the hard side of the HW but doable, discussion helpful, symbolic solutions are key, I would take this prof again.
pretty fair. do the homework and review it well and you will do fine.
Philips is very unforgiving and obsesses over the most minute details.
Very clear in explanation of material, tests cover exactly what is learned during class. No tricks. Would take another class with him.

Very articulate and very clear in explaining what he is deriving and why he is deriving it. Clean handwriting, class notes easy to follow. Tests are generally representative of the class work, including theoretical understanding.
